name: Parasect
flavorText: Mushroom-lacking specimens of this Pokemon lie unmoving in the forest, lending credence to the hypothesis that the large mushroom is in control of Parasect's actions.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may make both Active Pokemon Asleep and Poisoned.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Roserade
flavorText: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Charizard
flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Discard the other cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Leon card in your discard pile.

name: Chandelure
flavorText: This Pokemon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Gengar
flavorText: Possesses potential victims' shadows in an effort to steal away the victims' lives. If your shadow begins to laugh, you must take hold of a protective charm posthaste!
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in your discard pile, you may put it onto your Bench. If you do, put 3 damage counters on this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokemon for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Banette
flavorText: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.
Attack1Text: Put up to 7 damage counters on this Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter you placed in this way.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Hisuian Arcanine
flavorText: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.
Attack1Text: If you have no cards in your hand, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Spiritomb
flavorText: It lays curses by thinking wicked thoughts. Writings tell that this Pokemon was born out of the assembly of five score and eight malevolent spirits.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 more damage for each Spiritomb in your discard pile.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: This glutton appears in villages without warning and devours the entirety of their rice granariesâ€”such occurrences have long been counted among the gravest of disasters.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokemon done to this Pokemon. (Damage is not an effect.)
Attack1Text: This Pokemon is now Asleep. During Pokemon Checkup, flip 2 coins instead of 1. If either of them is tails, this Pokemon is still Asleep.

name: Castform
flavorText: Its form changes depending on the weather. The rougher conditions get, the rougher Castform's disposition!
Ability1Text: If you have 8 or more Stadium cards in your discard pile, ignore all Energy in this Pokemon's attack costs.
Attack1Text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

name: Orbeetle V
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Orbeetle VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Centiskorch V
Attack1Text: You may discard an Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Centiskorch VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon. If you did any damage with this attack, you may attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.

name: Pikachu V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Lightning Energy cards and attach them to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Pikachu VMAX
Attack1Text: You may discard all Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Enamorus V
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's Pokemon's Abilities done to each of your Pokemon that has any Psychic Energy attached, except any Enamorus V.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Gallade V
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Prize card you have taken.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Crobat V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. You can't use more than 1 Dark Asset Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Eternatus V
Attack1Text: You may attach a Darkness Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon VMAX, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Eternatus VMAX
Ability1Text: If all of your Pokemon in play are Darkness type, you can have up to 8 Pokemon on your Bench, and you can't put non-Darkness Pokemon into play. (If this Ability stops working, discard Pokemon from your Bench until you have 5.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Darkness Pokemon in play.

name: Pikachu VMAX
Attack1Text: You may discard all Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Mew VMAX
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your Benched Fusion Strike Pokemon's attacks and use it as this attack.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.
